cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper discusses a reinforcement learning method for training sequence generation models for structured output prediction problems, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper specifically focuses on policy-gradient approaches, which are commonly used in reinforcement learning, and proposes a new method that eliminates the need for warm-start training and sample variance reduction. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.CL, cs.CV, and cs.NE.
